result: blocked

## Diagnosis
Shine rendering is correct — verified visually by manually flying the camera to the latest node:
bright golden star with 4-point cross flare and warm halo at the centre of the canvas.
The bug is that flyCameraToNode() does NOT fire its camera animation on initial page load.

### Why flyCameraToNode fails
- File: code/memory-graph.html, function ~line 463-485
- tryFly rAF chain returns silently (without scheduling next frame) when
  node.x/y/z are not yet finite.
- On initial load the d3 simulation hasn't assigned positions yet when
  setShiningNode(latest) runs, so the first tryFly attempt bails.
- The 3.5s setTimeout safety net then either fires before coords are settled
  (fallback to origin) or fires too late (simulation has already settled
  far from origin).
- Net effect: camera stays at default (0,0,250) looking at origin.
- Latest node settles at world position ~(405, 1438, -76) → NDC (5.55, 15.64, 0.999)
  = completely offscreen.

### Verified healthy
- GET /api/memory-graph → 200, 895 nodes / 1126 edges (rendered view)
- Latest eligible node: task:MC-KANBAN-CREATE-20260627165916-74AF7F
  (kind=task, created 2026-06-27T16:59:16) — backend correct
- pickLatestNodeId exclusion list ['entity','project','tool','session','file'] — correct, DO NOT change
- Banner DOM: correctly shows "⭐ Latest ⭐ task:MC-KANBAN-CREATE-20260627…"
- __threeObj Group with halo Sprite (scale 31.9, opacity 0.76) + core Sprite (scale 72.2)
  both visible and in scene tree
- Manual Graph.cameraPosition({x,y,z+90}, target, 1000) → star renders perfectly centred

### Secondary issue
3x console warning "Multiple instances of Three.js being imported":
- vendor/three/three.min.js (rev ~150) loaded on line 243
- vendor/3d-force-graph bundles its own Three.js (rev 160) which then overwrites window.__THREE__
- Not the root cause of this bug, but a latent foot-gun; clean up by removing the standalone
  three.min.js script tag.

## Recommended fix (one file, code/memory-graph.html)

1. Remove line 243:
   <script src="vendor/three/three.min.js"></script>

2. In flyCameraToNode (~line 463), replace silent-bail with keep-polling in tryFly:
   // OLD:
   if (!Graph || !shiningNodeId || shiningNodeId !== nodeId) return;
   // NEW:
   if (!Graph || !shiningNodeId || shiningNodeId !== nodeId) {
     raf = requestAnimationFrame(tryFly);
     return;
   }
   // And inside, after locating the node:
   if (!node || !Number.isFinite(node.x)) {
     raf = requestAnimationFrame(tryFly);
     return;
   }

3. In the setTimeout safety net (~line 498-521), do not fall back to origin if coords
   aren't finite — keep polling until settled (cap at ~6s).

